s analysis of business systems through research, gathering and interpretation of data, development of alternatives and recommendations. Presents technical analysis and recommendations to management and may recommend alternatives. Works with business unit and IT to work through systems implementations, upgrades and problem resolution. Analyses include, but are not limited to, feasibility studies, cost/benefit analysis, trending/forecasting, financial analysis, budget analysis and reporting.</p><p style="height:6px;"></p><p>*_Responsibilities of this position include the following:_*</p><p style="height:6px;"></p><p>* Formulate and define systems scope and objectives through research and analysis using understanding of applicable business systems and industry requirements.</p><p style="height:6px;"></p><p>* Provide systems administration and process execution of management and maintenance systems.</p><p style="height:6px;"></p><p>* Develop or modify moderately complex information systems to meet business needs.</p><p style="height:6px;"></p><p>* Documents user and system requirements and revises existing system logic difficulties as necessary</p><p style="height:6px;"></p><p>* Coordinate and ensure quality and integrity of input data into operational and forecast systems.</p><p style="height:6px;"></p><p>* Provide data analysis for development and maintenance of modeling and reporting systems.</p><p style="height:6px;"></p><p>* Create tools to automate processes involving input and extraction of data and both regular and ad hoc reports.</p><p style="height:6px;"></p><p>* Analyze output data and reports and provide interpretation and concise communication of results.</p><p style="height:6px;"></p><p>*_Requirements for this position include the following:_*</p><p style="height:6px;"></p><p>* Bachelorâs Degree in Business, Computer Science, IT or a related field; or the equivalent combination of education and experience.</p><p style="height:6px;"></p><p>* A minimum of 